This paper deals with modeling techniques for hierarchical sequential data of different modalities, specifically video and text. The paper focuses on large-scale video and paragraph retrieval datasets and examines the effectiveness of learned embeddings when applied to downstream tasks such as zero-shot action recognition and video captioning. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are computer vision (cs.CV) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper proposes a generic model for embedding sequential data, which involves machine learning techniques such as deep learning, making it likely to fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with video data, which is a subset of multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
